<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10048b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10048b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10048b"> 48(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> curse evils of war / &amp; admire warlike / virtues</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">En effet, il est encore facile aujourd&apos;hui d&apos;y <font color="green">[dans un journal paru en 1536]</font> lire un long r&eacute;cit de la troisi&egrave;me guerre entre Charles-Quint et Fran&ccedil;ois I<sup>er</sup>, o&ugrave; il est dit comme conclusion: <mark>Tous les hommes maudissent les maux de la guerre et admirent les vertus guerri&egrave;res.</mark> <font color="green">[Indeed it is still easy to read in a journal that appeared in 1536 a long story of the third war between Charles V and Francis I which concludes: &ldquo;All men curse the evils of war and admire warlike virtues&rdquo;.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 85</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01021j" href="c01all.htm#c01021j">VI.C.01:021(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
